While rand volatility is moderating, the policy risks that helped spark the currency’s worst monthly sell-off this year show no sign of abating. South Africa’s political risk score as measured by GeoQuant indexes took a sharp step up in August as the ruling African National Congress forged ahead with a plan to seize white-owned land for redistribution. Investor concern that property rights may be undermined has knocked the rand at a time when Turkey’s woes already damped appetite for riskier assets, contributing to the South African currency’s 7.8 percent drop in August.